Git:

Git is a free and open source distributed version control system designed to handle everything from small to very large projects with speed and efficiency.

Creating a new git locally: 
git clone <url>
git init

Adding to staging:
git add .

Commiting:
git commit

Setting remote:
git remote add <remoteName> <url>
git push <remoteName>


Workflow:

1. git init
2. git add .
3. git commit -m "msg"
4. Create repository in github and copy url
5. Set up personal access token in github account
6. git remote add <remoteName> <remoteUrl>
7. git push <remoteName> <branch>
OR
7. 	a. git --set-upstream <remoteName> <branch> 
	b. git push

..............

Base folder: 

C:\Users\HOME\Desktop\knowledge-base>git add . & git commit -m "added more stuff" & git push